when components need to share data you really need to understand ",[47,52,53],{},"props"," and ",[47,56,57],{},"emit",".",[17,60,61],{},"In the upcoming posts you'll see the frontend pages already designed (but the code side isn't there yet, so don't worry — you won't suddenly find it all magically built). This series will move a bit slower from here because the frontend pages need time to plan and design.",{"title":63,"searchDepth":64,"depth":64,"links":65},"",2,[66,67],{"id":14,"depth":64,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":64,"text":23},"Vue","2019-08-04 15:27:25","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002Fvue-girlfriend-frontend-pages","1",{"title":6,"description":19},false,"en\u002FVue\u002Fvue-girlfriend-frontend-pages",[68,80],"Build a Girlfriend with Vue",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F04\u002Fvue-girlfriend-frontend-pages\u002F","kDfcWGojSqgTmGm5e5-_aNUlVH_QFX8ghn3Ho2M1JNY",{"newer":85,"older":89},{"url":86,"title":87,"date":88},"\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F07\u002Fdetails-when-inviting-speakers\u002F","The Many Small But Critical Details of Inviting Speakers","2019-08-07 15:21:42",{"url":90,"title":91,"date":92},"\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2019\u002F08\u002F03\u002Fpure-css-heart-drawing\u002F","Drawing a Heart in Pure CSS","2019-08-03 16:40:36",[94,99,103],{"url":95,"title":96,"date":97,"readingMinutes":98},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F04\u002Fvue-nuxt-project-folder-structure\u002F","Vue\u002FNuxt Project Architecture: How to Pick the Right Folder Structure for Your Team","2025-12-04 11:40:56","7",{"url":100,"title":101,"date":102,"readingMinutes":98},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2025\u002F11\u002F06\u002Fvue-sfc-spec-block-for-ai-development\u002F","Use a Custom &lt;spec lang=\"md\"&gt; Block in Vue SFC for Smoother AI Development","2025-11-06 13:45:34",{"url":104,"title":105,"date":106,"readingMinutes":107},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2025\u002F02\u002F16\u002Fvue3-shallowref-vs-ref\u002F","shallowRef: Another Way to Declare Re